# Tacocat Boutique Server

# Introduction
This is a simple REST server that is used during Aickathon 2018

# Installation
1. clone the repository
2. cd into the directory
3. run `pip install -r requirements.txt`
4. run `python src/main.py`
5. take note of the url address in console (or usually url is YOUR_IP:5000)

# Available Request
1. Create new user
  - Description: Create a new user with a name. Remember to save the user_id to reference back the user
  - URL = `/newuser`
  - Method = POST
  - data parameter
  ```
  {"user_name": [string]}
  ```
  - success response
  ```
    {"user_id": id, 
      "user": {
        "name": [name],
        "photos": [],
        "top_colors": [],
        "top_colors_hex": [],
        "top_garment": [],
        "top_styles": []
        }
      }
  ```
 2. Add a new photo
  - Description: Add a new photo to the user_id, automatic call fashion api 
  - URL = `/newphoto`
  - Method = POST
  - data parameter
  ```
  {"user_id": [int],
   "img_data": [base64 data]
   }
  ```
  - success response
  ```
    {'message': 'success'}
  ```
 3. Get user details
  - Description: Get all user details including all photos uploaded. Photo has almost the same structure as here https://recoqnitics.com/guide/fashion-api.html. Note: photo_data is base64 encoded
  - URL = `/getuser`
  - Method = POST
  - data parameter
  ```
  {"user_id": [int]}
  ```

 4. Get user top preferences
  - Description: Call this to calculate and return the user top preference. All is sorted descendingly (most preferred to least).
  - URL = `/getusertop`
  - Method = POST
  - data parameter
  ```
  {"user_id": [integer]}
  ```
  - success response
  ```
    {
    "top_colors": [
        "Olive Green Dark",
        "Warm Grey",
        "Ivory Black"
    ],
    "top_colors_hex": [
        "#625149",
        "#887b72",
        "#2f3033"
    ],
    "top_garments": [
        "Tee"
    ],
    "top_styles": [
        "90s",
        "Rocker",
        "Outdoor"
    ],
    "user_id": 0
  }
  ```

  6. Get suggestion by uploading a single photo
  - Description: Get suggestion by uploading a photo. Suggestion is based on style and color of the photo uploaded
  - URL = `/suggestwithphoto`
  - Method = POST
  - data parameter
  ```
  {"user_id": [integer],
   "img_data: [base64 data]
  }
  ```
  - success response
    - same as API no 5
 
# Error Handling
  - If error occurred, a response body with json format as below will be returned.
  ```
  {"error": [error message]}
  ```
